# =============================================================================
# Lumina .gitignore — what to NOT upload to GitHub.
#
# Audited on 2026-04-25. Three classes of exclusions:
#   1. Build artifacts and dependencies (regenerable)
#   2. Secrets, credentials, environment overrides (leak risk)
#   3. License-sensitive user-supplied assets (.vrm, .vrma — per author terms)
#
# Anything not covered here lands in git. If you find yourself running
# `git add -f` on something, ask first whether it really should ship.
# =============================================================================


# --- Node / Next.js build artifacts ------------------------------------------
node_modules/
.next/
out/
.vercel/
*.tsbuildinfo
build/
coverage/
.pnp/
.pnp.js
.pnpm-debug.log*

# Lockfiles for tools we don't use (keep package-lock.json)
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml


# --- Environment overrides + likely secret-bearing files ---------------------
# `.local` suffix is the Next.js convention for "this machine only". Never
# commit any of these. Empty .env (no suffix) is also blocked because users
# put keys there too.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development.local
.env.production.local
.env.test.local

# Common credential file shapes — even if we don't use them today, drift
# happens. Block at the file-extension and filename-substring levels.
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.cer
*.crt
*credentials*
*secrets*
id_rsa
id_rsa.*
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.*
.ssh/

# Database files — block in case anyone drops a sqlite snapshot
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.mdb


# --- Logs and runtime files --------------------------------------------------
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
/tmp/
/tmp/buddy-bridge*.log
/tmp/lumina-*.log
.DS_Store


# --- Auto-generated reasoning logs (Claude Code session telemetry) -----------
# Match at any depth — the harness writes these into multiple locations.
**/reasoninghist/


# --- License-sensitive assets ------------------------------------------------
# Each .vrm is governed by its original author's terms (VRoid Hub / Booth /
# Mixamo / etc.). Tracking them in git risks accidental redistribution —
# even when the author allows personal use, they often forbid republishing.
# Keep .vrm/.vrma files locally only.
#
# `idle_loop.vrma` is the upstream default (MIT-licensed, ships with
# ChatVRM) and is allow-listed so a fresh clone has a working idle loop.
# Anything else under public/vrma/ is user-added and must be ignored.
**/*.vrm
**/*.vrm.bak
src/web/public/vrma/
src/web/public/vrm/
!src/web/public/idle_loop.vrma

# Personality JSON files ARE tracked — they're project source.
# (No exclusion for src/web/public/personalities/*.json — committed.)

# --- C# launcher build output ------------------------------------------------
src/launcher/bin/
src/launcher/obj/
src/launcher/publish/

# --- LuminaLauncher runtime data (user-specific) ----------------------------
lumina-prefs.json
lumina-debug.txt

# --- WebView2 cache (created next to LuminaLauncher.exe) --------------------
*.exe.WebView2/

# --- Terminal server node_modules (rebuilt on first run) --------------------
src/terminal/node_modules/

# --- Claude Code project instructions (machine-specific, not for public repo) -
CLAUDE.md

# --- Debug logs --------------------------------------------------------------
lumina-hook-debug.log


# --- IDE / editor scratch ----------------------------------------------------
.idea/
.vs/
*.iml
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.bak
.vscode/settings.local.json
.vscode/launch.local.json
.vscode/*.local.json


# --- Dev-time scratch (typecheck commands during sessions) -------------------
# `tsc --noEmit -p tsconfig.<scratch>.json` is a common iteration pattern.
# Block names we've used; legitimate per-package tsconfigs use different
# names (tsconfig.build.json, tsconfig.test.json) and are not blocked.
src/web/tsconfig.buddy.json
src/web/tsconfig.lumina.json


# --- Compiled binaries / archives that shouldn't end up here -----------------
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.zip
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.rar
*.7z
*.iso


# --- OS noise ----------------------------------------------------------------
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
$RECYCLE.BIN/


# --- Lumina-specific scratch -------------------------------------------------
# Demo recording outputs (avoid committing 50 MB of GIF accidentally)
demo/
*.mov
*.mp4
docs/demo.gif
!docs/demo.gif.placeholder
